added.title: P.P.
added.description: While stopping a museum theft, the Titans encounter the P.P. Goblin, who uses the Titan's pet peeves against them.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: Lil' Dimples
added.description: Thinking it's a way to reconnect with her father, Raven enters a beauty pageant.

added.title: Demon Prom
added.description: Trigon makes Raven attend her prom and she brings along the other Titans to upset him.

added.title: Rad Dudes with Bad Tudes
added.description: After seeing a pair of cool dudes on rollerblades, Robin tries to be just like them.

added.title: Caramel Apples
added.description: Raven and Starfire clash after Starfire creates a bond with Raven's father, while Robin, Cyborg, and Beast Boy struggle to return to Earth's surface after falling into a deep cavern.

added.title: Crazy Day
added.description: It's Crazy Day again and Raven must do her best to avoid being driven crazy by the other Titans.

added.title: Thanksgiving
added.description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

added.title: Nean
added.description: Raven is cursed to be nice; meanwhile, Starfire is about to marry a pot of chili.

added.title: Driver's Ed
added.description: Robin is inadvertently the getaway driver for a bank robbery in the midst of his driver's ed exam.

added.title: Dreams
added.description: A glimpse inside each Titan's dream world.

added.title: Ranger Norm
added.description: When Tabes leaves for a conference, the Bears have to deal with her substitute, Ranger Norm.

added.title: Snake Babies
added.description: Charlie adopts baby snakes despite the Bears thinking he's not ready for parenthood.

added.title: Bros in the City
added.description: The Bears star in a reality TV show along with Griff, Tom, and Isaac.

added.title: Lord of the Poppies
added.description: Grizz and the Poppy Rangers go camping on an island, but they soon find themselves deserted.

added.title: Band of Outsiders
added.description: A gang of streetwise kids takes Baby Ice Bear under their wing.

added.title: Panda's Birthday
added.description: For Panda's Birthday, the Bears try to help Panda meet his favorite K-Pop band, Monsta X.

added.title: Googs
added.description: The Bears win a tour of the infamous Googs corporate headquarters.

added.title: Bear Squad
added.description: Tabes deputizes the Bears so they can go to the city and catch a thief.

added.title: I, Butler
added.description: The Bears use a robot bear to help around the house. But things get tricky when they lose control of the robot.

added.title: Best Bears
added.description: The Bears must complete their Best-Man duties on the day of Darrell's wedding.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Shush Ninjas
added.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: The Lady
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin track a women emerging from their home, they discover her to be a member of a gang of wise-cracking elderly friends. However, as they get closer and closer to her life, they realize they may know her already.

added.title: The Neighbor
added.description: When their neighbor tries to bring over a package for them, Gumball and Darwin realize they have never learned his name, and it's way too late to ask. They try everything to figure out what it is, but when they do they find out there are bigger secrets to learn about their neighbor than just his name...

added.title: The Slip
added.description: Richard doesn't answer the door in time and the jobsworth delivery guy will not let him have his package. His options are to pick his package up at the depot or pay for a redelivery. Richard doesn't like the sound of either option, so a battle of wills begins that can only end in the destruction of one or both of them.

added.title: The Outside
added.description: The family goes to visit Richard's Dad. Based on his basic living standards and extended absence from Richard's life, they assume Frankie must have done a stretch in the slammer. When Frankie comes to stay with the Wattersons, they decide the way to make him comfortable is to make him uncomfortable and turn their house into a prison.

added.title: The Routine
added.description: Mom and the kids depart for their hard day's work, leaving a seemingly lazy Dad half-asleep on the sofa. Mom has given him one very simple job: buy mayonnaise. However, Dad manages to turn this mundane task into an epic quest, showing that his daily routine isn't as inactive as his family imagine.

added.title: The Coach
added.description: The new coach at Elmore High stands up to Jamie. The new Coach witnesses Jamie bullying the other kids at lunch and steps in. Jamie is made to apologise, much to the amazement of the other kids. Gumball and Darwin worry about Jamie seeking revenge, especially when they see him sneaking into the back of Coach's car. They use their newly acquired gym skills to save the Coach from being bullied.

added.title: The Joy
added.description: Miss Simian has to save herself from a contagious Joy virus infecting the whole school. After Dad gives Gumball and Darwin a special hug, the kids go to school filled with a virulent form of Joy. Miss Simian quickly identifies the terrible affliction, and soon enough it spreads to the other kids. She has to find a cure before it's too late. Before Ms Simian herself is won over by . . . Joy.

added.title: The Bros
added.description: Darwin gets jealous of Gumball and Penny's relationship. When Darwin and Gumball reveal how they'd spend their perfect day, Gumball confesses that he would spend it with Penny. Darwin gets jealous and sets out to dig some dirt on Penny, hoping it will split them up. Meanwhile Gumball is planning to step his and Penny's relationship up a notch . . . by proposing marriage!

added.title: The Man
added.description: It's Granny Jojo's Birthday and she's brought an unexpected guest to dinner. Granny Jojo has brought a boyfriend to her birthday meal and Dad isn't happy about it. He bans Granny JoJo from ever seeing Louis again. When the kids get caught sneaking Granny Jojo out of the house, Dad challenges Louis to a man-off to prove once and for all who is the man of the house?!!

added.title: The Job
added.description: Dad gets his first job as a pizza delivery guy, which rocks the very fabric of the universe.

added.title: The Remote
added.description: The Wattersons' battle for possession of the TV remote gets dirty.

added.title: The Hero
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are determined to prove to their dad that he is their hero, at any cost!

added.title: The Castle
added.description: When Mom is away "anything goes" and Dad's lack of rules soon attracts unwelcome houseguests.

added.title: The Mustache
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's wish comes true when they suddenly turn into men.

added.title: Chicken in Chichen Itza Part 1: Pyramid Scheme
added.description: Team Tennyson visits the monuments of Chichen Itza, but when Ben learns about the possible existence of a mythical creature, the Quetzalcoatl, the hero takes it upon himself to find the feathered serpent himself.

added.title: Chicken in Chichen Itza Part 2: The Wages of Fear
added.description: Team Tennyson help transport a caged Quetzalcoatl through the Yucatan jungle, only to encounter a saboteur, La Grange, who hijacks the precious cargo and leads our heroes on a high-octane off-road chase!

added.title: Ben in Rome Part 1: A Slice of Life
added.description: Team Tennyson's quest for the best pizza in Rome leads them to the Bugg Brothers and their latest culinary caper, complete with stolen recipes, kidnapped chefs, shrunken landmarks, and a high-speed chase around the Eternal City.

added.title: Ben in Rome Part 2: The Bee's Knees
added.description: On vacation in Rome, Gwen takes Team Tennyson on a self-guided tour of the many ancient sites, but when a distracted Ben accidentally stumbles upon Queen Bee's monumental heist, the hero must work together with his family if he is to save the city from being sacked for the first time in centuries!

added.title: Tokyo Fun Part 1: Big Bugg Bash
added.description: While in Tokyo, Team Tennyson comes face to face with a horrible secret, Japan's hottest new restaurant is being run by the Bugg Brothers as a nefarious scheme to make loads of money off an unsuspecting public.

added.title: Don't Laze Me, Bro
added.description: Ben and his arch-enemy Billy Billions clash in a duel for supremacy at the world's largest Laser Tag Park, LASER TOWN. But, when Billy inadvertently ignites a robot rebellion, and the lasers are set from tag to disintegrate, their childish game escalates into a full blown war! The two foes find that they must set aside their petty differences and team up in order to make it out alive, let alone save the day!

added.title: Don't Let the Bass Drop
added.description: Ben and Gwen are excited to attend an Earth Day EDM concert in Portland until the show is hijacked by the sound-manipulating baddy Lord Decibel who uses sound as a weapon to trash the planet.

added.title: Bad Penny
added.description: Ben is at the annual Big Bacon Pig Parade, but childhood friend Penny Heaven has met the family to ruin Ben's fun with her safety-obsessed self. While dodging Penny's overzealous safety precautions, Ben uncovers a plot by the Bug Brothers to steal helium from the parade balloons to rob banks with! Penny's badgering turns the heist into an accidental kidnapping so Ben must not only stop the robbery but save his least favorite safety monitor in the process.

added.title: Zombozo-Land
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Max revisit their favorite amusement park, renovated and re-branded as AdrenaWORLD! Unfortunately, the new management is Zombozo and his trio of new henchmen! He's got a plan to hypnotize everyone in the park to form a criminal army. Ben has to set aside his desire to ride every ride in the park and make things right.

added.title: Forgeti
added.description: When Gwen drags Ben along on a hike in search of the legendary Forgeti, a yeti that makes people forget they ever saw it, Ben is dubious. But with Dr. Animo on the trail of the mythical beast as well, what looks like a hoax becomes a hero time adventure for the ages, if Ben can remember it ever happened.

added.title: Max to the Max
added.description: While Ben, Gwen, and Max hike to a waterfall, the Bugg Brothers are back with a plan to duplicate Diamondhead; but when their cloning ray gun fires on Max instead, multiplying him endlessly, Gwen and Ben must round up all the Maxes while also fighting off the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Cutting Corners
added.description: Ben approaches Geezer Bob about doing a little yard work to earn spending money, but when Ben goes Upgrade to transform the lawnmower into a super fast mowing machine, he accidentally draws the ire of Bob's gnome-neighbors, the tiny, terrifyingly tenacious Billy-Bob Goblins.

added.title: Xingo
added.description: Ben is more interested in a marathon of his favorite cartoon show, "Xingo", but when Ben goes Upgrade to get a better signal, the titular Xingo leaps from his animated dimension to ours, bringing mad chaos with him!

added.title: Scared Silly
added.description: When the Rust Bucket runs out of gas on a foggy East Coast road, Ben, Gwen and Max are forced to stay at a hotel being menaced by Creepy Carl, a local folklore expert, who may actually be a ghost!

added.title: Need for Speed
added.description: Touring Yellowstone, Ben uncovers a plot by the fast & furious LaGrange to find treasure buried below the national park, but with a little help from Old Faithful, Overflow is able to douse LaGrange's dreams.

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: Creek Daycare
added.description: Craig and his sister, Jessica, try their hand at running the daycare at the Creek.

added.title: Sugar Smugglers
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP become smugglers to sneak candy to kids in need.

added.title: Ferret Quest
added.description: The kids are on the search for an elusive ferret in the Creek.  Kelsey unites her friends Stacks and Wildernessa to find it, but worries they'd rather hangout with each other instead of her.

added.title: Itch to Explore
added.description: Craig's quest to map the entire Creek takes him and his friends into the treacherous Poison Ivy Grove.

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Broken Back Kotter
added.description: Izzy nominates Chef for the Daycare Professional of the Year award and will do whatever it takes to see him win. As it turns out, it takes a lot.

added.title: Weekend at Buddy's
added.description: After Cody's best friend doll breaks on their watch, Owen and Beth put themselves in grave danger while trying to do the right thing.

added.title: MacArthur Park
added.description: After losing countless jobs because of the kids, MacArthur shows up at the school seeking revenge.

added.title: Last Mom Standing
added.description: When Chef's Mom and Leshawna's Grandmother drop their loved ones off at the same time, it kicks off a dangerous competition for who is the most caring mother-figure.

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Fart
added.description: After accidentally swallowing her first loose tooth and fearing that means no cash under the pillow, Leshawna tries to capture the tooth fairy. Instead, she accidentally captures the fart fairy. This comes with great consequence.

added.title: Dissing Cousins Part 1
added.description: It's International Cousins Day and Owen and Gwen are dreading the fact that their cousins Max and Ella are spending the day with them. And soon everyone else will understand why.

added.title: Dissing Cousins Part 2
added.description: It's International Cousins Day and Owen and Gwen are dreading the fact that their cousins Max and Ella are spending the day with them. And soon everyone else will understand why.

added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Block Party
added.description: Apple and Onion have to outwit a mean duck who's taken over their building's roof.

added.title: Party Popper
added.description: Apple and Onion's party plans are interrupted by a grumpy guest.

added.title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
added.description: Apple and Onion must conquer their obsessions of sausages and a video game.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish
added.description: Apple and Onion have to prove that they're not selfish when they do their good deeds.

added.title: The Inbetween
added.description: Apple and Onion get lost beneath their floorboards and must find a way out.

added.title: Election Day
added.description: Apple runs for Mayor.

added.title: La Planchada
added.description: When Vic gets the chicken pox and is forbidden from playing in a tag tournament, he summons a mythical ghost nurse to cure him.

added.title: Folk Art Foes
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes the lord of mischief from an ancient relic, V and V have to work together to trap it back inside.

added.title: Brotherly Love
added.description: After breaking Chata's plant, Vic and Val must accomplish the seemingly easy task of replacing it; this proves difficult when their squabbling puts Monte Macabre in jeopardy.

added.title: Chata's Quinta Quinceañera
added.description: Vic and Val want to go to a friend's pool party on the same day as their grandma's quinceañera, so they use a magical flute that allows them to teleport and attend both at the same time.

added.title: Cleaning Day
added.description: Victor & Valentino gain a newfound respect for cleanliness after Chata's house traps them inside its labyrinth of ancient, magical walls.

added.title: Hurricane Chata
added.description: When V & V discover that Chata's emotions control the water in the lake, they use it to their advantage and start their own wave pool business.

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club
added.description: Instead of celebrating Valentine's Day, Vic & Val take on a dare to explore a haunted mansion with their rivals, Charlene & Pineapple.

added.title: The Boy Who Cried Lechuza
added.description: After faking an injury to get out of work, Vic gains sympathy from everyone while unknowingly attracting attention from a dangerous mythical creature.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val holds a grudge against Vic, unwittingly attracting an evil cadejo, a mythological wolf-like beast.

added.title: A New Don
added.description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

added.title: Know It All
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes evil bats from a cave, it's up to the boys and Don to protect the town, but Vic's know-it-all attitude keeps getting in the way.

added.title: Love at First Bite
added.description: Val crushes on a girl named Matty, who Vic is suspicious of but Val ignores his warnings. When Val goes to dinner at her house she turns into a Matlazihua and he discovers he's what's for dinner!

added.title: Wasted True Potential
added.description: In the wake of the previous season's victory, the ninja have gone soft and Master Wu must remind them of who they truly are.

added.title: Questing For Quests
added.description: Realizing they have gone soft, the ninja search for a quest to reignite their Spinjitzu training. Unfortunately, NINJAGO City is enjoying a period of rare tranquility.

added.title: A Rocky Start
added.description: The ninja have found their quest! Now they just have to get there, which involves a road trip through the Desert of Doom, a region supposedly inhabited by a giant scarab beetle.

added.title: The Belly of the Beast
added.description: To repair the Land-Bounty, the ninja must retrieve a critical engine component that has been swallowed by a giant scarab beetle.

added.title: Booby-Traps, and How To Survive Them
added.description: The ninja team up with a reluctant Clutch Powers to enter a mysterious pyramid where they inadvertently unleash an ancient evil.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Everything's Fine
added.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

added.title: #DCSuperHeroBoys Part 1
added.description: What begins as a simple vandalism investigation becomes an all-out turf war when the team encounters a powerful trio of Kryptonians bent on world domination, and, perhaps even worse, a rival team of SUPER HERO BOYS!

added.title: #MisgivingTree
added.description: Jessica Cruz and Pam Isley bond over protecting an ancient tree from being cut down. Neither of them realizes who the other's alter ego is, or the lengths to which they'll go to protect what's important.

added.title: #IllusionsOfGrandeur
added.description: Ready to emerge from her father's shadow, Zee Zatara secretly seeks fame and acclaim performing for her own audience at the pier. But when her act is dismissed as fakery, she loses her cool and accidentally unleashes mischievous gremlins who run wild all over the pier.

added.title: #BeastsInShow
added.description: When Babs and Kara spar over whose dog is better, they decide to settle it at the Metropolis Dog Show, where Ace the Bat-Hound and Krypto the Superdog suddenly find themselves called upon to save the day… in more ways than one.

added.title: #GothamCon
added.description: A fun day for Barbara Gordon and her bestie Harleen Quinzel (at Gotham City's annual geekfest, the Annual Convention of Gotham City Enthusiats!) is turned on its head when, out of nowhere, the villainous Harley Quinn shows up to wreak havoc! Lucky for everyone, Batgirl just happens to be in the area...

added.title: Snarf's Day Off
added.description: Hey everyone, it's Snarf's monthly day off! That's right, this episode follows Snarf as he leaves Cats' Lair to get a needed vacation, by transforming into a normal cat and hanging out with a nice old lady on a farm! But his relaxing day is threatened when Snarf and the nice old lady cross paths with Mumm-Ra!

added.title: Mandora's Law
added.description: Tygra creates a bunch of new laws for Third Earth so Mandora can finally arrest the Mutants. Unfortunately the Thundercats are really bad at following their own rules and the Mutants are really good at working around them.

added.title: Thunder Road
added.description: When a crate containing fifty Swords of Omen lands on Third Earth, the ThunderCats rush out in the ThunderTank to find them. Unfortunately The Mutants and Mumm-Ra want those swords too so it's going to be a race to get to them! A wacky race, you might say. We won't say that, but you might.

added.title: Corporate Buyout
added.description: The Cheetara Corp employee retreat gets canceled when Baron Karnon, a mysterious corporate raider, buys them out! Now Cheetara and Jan-Jan must brave the wilds of Third Earth's most dangerous jungles to find the Baron's office and demand a meeting with the man who stole their company!

added.title: Hachiman
added.description: While on a super important mission to get batteries for the TV remote Lion-O meets Hachiman, a cool Samurai warrior. Now Lion-O will do anything to prove he's just as cool as Hachiman, even if it means risking his own life!

added.title: Gemcation
added.description: Greg and the Gems take Steven on vacation to help him relax.

added.title: Hit the Diamond
added.description: Steven and the Gems play an old fashioned game of baseball.

added.title: Steven Floats
added.description: Steven is so excited to be back home that he jumps for joy and jumps way too high.

added.title: Drop Beat Dad
added.description: Steven helps Sour Cream put on a show, even though Sour Cream's stepdad doesn't approve of DJs.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: The Answer
added.description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

added.title: Jail Break
added.description: Steven teams up with a new ally to rescue the Gems.

added.title: I Love You Mao Mao
added.description: An explosive loner and his slacker best friend are waylaid from their journey into legend, only to find that their story is just beginning.

added.title: The Perfect Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.

added.title: Ultraclops
added.description: Badgerclops gets huge to destroy a towering monster, but when he refuses to shrink down, the kingdom faces a new terror.

added.title: Not Impressed
added.description: When a Sweetypie isn't impressed with the sheriff dept's antics, our three heroes try everything to win him over.

added.title: Enemy Mime
added.description: When the Sheriff's Dept fights a monster that copies their every move, they'll have to find a way to fight without fighting.

added.title: Bao Bao's Revenge
added.description: When Mao Mao's old partner threatens the kingdom, his friends will need to learn about his past in order to protect the present.

added.title: All By Mao Self
added.description: Mao Mao's desire to be a legend drives him to keep topping himself. But how much is enough?

added.title: The Ultimate Adventure: Come Along with Me
added.description: The fate of Ooo is revealed to two adventurers in the distant future. Princess Bubblegum gathers her allies while Finn searches for a way to prevent the coming Great Gum War.

added.title: Ketchup
added.description: BMO and Marceline swap stories about their recent adventures.

added.title: Stakes Part 1: Marceline the Vampire Queen
added.description: Finn & Jake hunt for a shadowy predator and Marceline asks Princess Bubblegum for a huge favor.

added.title: Stakes Part 8: The Dark Cloud
added.description: The final confrontation! Who will survive?

added.title: Sky Witch
added.description: Marceline is on a top-secret mission tracking Maja the Sky Witch. When she loses the witch's trail, Marceline turns to Princess Bubblegum for help.

added.title: The Pit
added.description: Kee-Oth the Blood Demon has kidnapped Jake, taken him back to his dimension and thrown him in a pit. If Finn wants to rescue his friend, he's going to need Lady Rainicorn's help and a videotape that will reveal how to open the portal to Kee-Oth's dimension.

added.title: Dad's Dungeon
added.description: Jake's Dad appears in a holographic message with a mysterious challenge for Finn and Jake.

added.title: Crystals Have Power
added.description: Jake takes a vow of non-violence, which is inconvenient when they're attacked by marauders from the crystal dimension.

added.title: Pool Duel
added.description: Unikitty and the gang are having a great time at the public pool, until they try to get Puppycorn to swim in the deep end with them. Puppycorn is terrified of the deep end. Now Unikitty and the gang must get him over his fear, so he can have maximum pool fun. Meanwhile, Master Frown and Brock are hatching a plan to ruin everyone's fun, by pulling the pool's plug.

added.title: This Spells Disaster
added.description: The gang is planning a surprise for Puppycorn, so they spell things out when talking so he won't find out. Desperate to know what they're saying, Puppycorn finds a magic book that he thinks will help him learn to spell, but unbeknownst to him, it's teaching him how to cast spells! Will Puppycorn realize that knowledge is power and some secrets are kept for a reason?

added.title: Trapped in Paradise
added.description: Unikitty and the gang have crashed on a fabulous island. It's really nice and no one wants to leave until Richard convinces them that they need to return to the Kingdom and deal with their responsibilities. Unfortunately every attempt to escape the island is sabotaged. Now they must find the culprit to ensure their return home.

added.title: Volcano
added.description: A super-grumpy volcano appears in the kingdom, so Unikitty takes the gang on an epic quest to cheer it up with one of FeeBee's flowers before it erupts and destroys the kingdom.

added.title: Beach Daze
added.description: Unikitty and the gang gear up for a fun day at the beach... but when Master Frown shows up as the lifeguard to spoil their plans in the sand, Unikitty and the gang embark on a beach quest to find the legendary Perfect Spot, far away from Frown's tyrannical rule. But can they get there before Frown and claim it for their own or will their quest turn out to be a real beach bummer?

added.title: Tragic Magic
added.description: After Richard puts on an amateur magic show, Dr. Fox becomes obsessed with figuring out how his science-defying tricks are done. But as she sets about using all of her genius intellect finding experimental ways to pull off the little pup's party tricks, will she accidentally ruin the wonder of magic?

added.title: Landlord Lord
added.description: The Land Lord has threatened Master Frown and Brock with eviction unless they fix the damage they've done to their apartment. Worried, Brock invites Unikitty and the gang to help. Instead of doing what the guys want to their place, she proceeds to do what she wants. Realizing her error, she returns the apartment to its former disgusting state, but now Frown and Brock are in danger of eviction again. They must team up with Unikitty and the gang to battle the Land Lord and save their home.

added.title: Space Mission: Danger
added.description: After their spaceship explodes, Unikitty and the gang float helplessly through space. As they try to formulate a plan that will get them home safe, they flash back to how each of them is responsible for their ship being destroyed. Will they make it home, and more importantly who will be to blame if they don't.

added.title: BatKitty
added.description: The gang are at the local laundromat cleaning their clothes, when Unikitty finds Batman's uniform mixed in with her clothes.  Intoxicated by the coolness of it, Unikitty takes on the persona of Batman and begins to fight crime.  When she accidentally causes Master Frown to step up his crime game, she will need the help of her friends, dressed as Robin, to stop him.

added.title: Primogenita
added.description: El Emperador Garmadon ha tomado el control de Ciudad Ninjago donde Lloyd se retira hacia las sombras. Mientras tanto, los otros Ninjas y Wu Joven quedan varados en el Reino de Oni y Dragón y descubren que no están solos.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Firstbourne
added.description: Emperor Garmadon has taken control of Ninjago City where Lloyd retreats to the shadows. Meanwhile, the other Ninja and Young Wu are shipwrecked in the Realm of Oni & Dragon and find they are not alone.

added.title: Iron & Stone
added.description: Cole and Young Wu attempt to free their friends, who have been taken captive by a tribe of Dragon Hunters. Meanwhile in Ninjago, Lloyd is reunited with some old friends who may prove valuable allies against Emperor Garmadon.

added.title: Hierro y piedra
added.description: Cole y Wu Joven intentan liberar a sus amigos, que han sido capturados por una tribu de Cazadores de Dragones. Mientras tanto en Ninjago, Lloyd se reúne con unos viejos amigos que quizás sean aliados valiosos contra el Emperador Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Radio Ninjago libre
added.description: Lloyd deberá encontrar su voz mientras lidera una pequeña resistencia para capturar las señales de transmisión en Ciudad Ninjago. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, el Barón de Hierro lleva a los Ninjas en una cacería de dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Radio Free NinjaGo
added.description: Lloyd must find his voice as he leads a small resistance to capture the airwaves in Ninjago City. Meanwhile in the First Realm, Iron Baron takes the Ninja on a dragon hunt.

added.title: Como construir un dragon
added.description: Mientras Lloyd y los rebeldes celebran su exitoso golpe contra el Emperador Garmadon, en el Reino de Oni y Dragón, los Ninjas se aventuran con un elaborado escape de las garras del Barón de Hierro y sus Cazadores de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: How to Build a Dragon
added.description: While Lloyd and the rebels celebrate their successful strike against Emperor Garmadon, in the Realm of Oni and Dragon, the Ninja dare an elaborate escape from the clutches of Iron Baron and his Dragon Hunters.

added.title: El camino dorado
added.description: El cuartel general de la resistencia es irrumpido y Lloyd lucha por no ser capturado. Mientras tanto, los Ninjas son capturados por Heavy-Metal, pero encuentran un aliado improbable.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Gilded Path
added.description: The headquarters to the resistance is breached and Lloyd scrambles to avoid capture. Meanwhile, the Ninja are caught by Heavy Metal, but find an unlikely ally.

added.title: New Direction
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the best directors in the business help a kid in need of acting lessons become a star.

added.title: King Gus
added.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.

added.title: Red Action 3: Grudgement Day
added.description: KO and Enid attempt to prevent a mysterious power battle between Rad and Red Action.

added.title: Fleas Help Me
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang help their K9 pal, Charlie Burgers, get rid of his flea infestation.

added.title: Champion of the Universe, Dan!/Operation Babysitter
added.description: Champion of the Universe, Dan!: Dan starts "sleep brawling", rolling out Drago causing damage and confusion while he's fast asleep. With the help of a "sleep expert", Ajit attempts to stop Dan and put his "sleep brawling" to rest once and for all./Operation Babysitter: Ajit lands a job babysitting a rambunctious toddler - Aiden. Having no experience with kids, Ajit recruits Wynton to help him out. Things get a little out of hand when Aiden rolls out - Krakelious. Now, Ajit and Wynton have a tiny Baku-brawler on their hands, with no way to stop him!

added.title: Beastie Team Battle/Ajit and Lia
added.description: Beastie Team Battle: China Riot is on the lookout for a partner to team up with in the new Bakugan battle team tournament being held in Los Volmos. Riot may have only been after a brawling partner, but ends up with a new friend./Ajit and Lia: Lia knows the story of where Ajit found his Golden Baku-balls, but no one knows "how" he's able to partner with Golden Bakugan. To get the inside scoop, Lia tags along with Ajit at his new job as a security guard at the local Museum.

added.title: Once More into the Maze/Grandpas in the Wild
added.description: Once More into the Maze: Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett were spotted at the ruins where the great core cell is housed! Alarmed by the report from Benton Dusk, the Awesome Brawlers head to the Yucatan Peninsula to investigate./Grandpas in the Wild: During an all-out brawl with Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, the Awesome Brawlers are hit with an attack that sends everyone spiraling to various parts of the maze. Split up from the rest of the gang, Wynton and Lightning find themselves in a strange unfamiliar part of the maze. While trying to get their bearings, they discover some new golden allies.

added.title: The Past Revealed/Run! A Storm's on the Way
added.description: The Past Revealed: After getting lost in maze with Lia, Ajit remembers the day he met Pharol and Auxilataur. He finally can explain how he was able to partner with golden Bakugan, but Ajit's story is interrupted by a familiar face - Storm!/Run! A Storm's on the Way: Still upset that Ajit has given up his life as a phantom thief, Storm rolls out Hydranoid x Aquos and attacks! Ajit and Lia take off running through the maze as Storm gives chase.

added.title: Golden Bakugan Encounter/Ties of Gold
added.description: Golden Bakugan Encounter: Dan and Shun, split up from the rest of Awesome Brawlers, are traveling in through the maze when they discover McQ. It turns out McQ is seeking a golden Bakugan. When the boys go in for a closer look, they are startled by an old friend, and together confront McQ./Ties of Gold: The now reunited Awesome Brawlers are once again confronted by Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, who are on the hunt for golden Bakugan. With tired Bakugan, the Awesome Brawlers will have to give it their all to defend against this evil.

added.title: Diversion en Tokio, Parte 1: Ataque de los Bichos
added.description: En una visita a Tokio, el equipo de Tennyson se enfrenta a un secreto horrible: los Bugg Brothers están manejando el nuevo restaurante de moda en Japón como parte de un plan perverso para ganar un montón de dinero a costa de un público desprevenido.

added.title: Cambio de Temporada
added.description: Cuando nuestros héroes regresan de sus vacaciones, K.O. se horroriza al descubrir que las cosas cambiaron.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Seasons Change
added.description: When our heroes return from time off, KO is horrified to discover that things have changed.

added.title: Festival de Cine en la Plaza
added.description: Cuando se organiza un festival de cine propio en la Plaza, iEnid y Rad están seguros de que su obra ganará!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Plaza Film Festival
added.description: When the plaza has its own film festival, KO, Enid and Rad are sure their entry will win!

added.title: Freedom Cactus
added.description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Red Action to the Future
added.description: When Red Action is called to the future for an epic battle, Enid is unsure of what to do.

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Company Man
added.description: When Clarence loses the ball during a soccer game, he ends up following it into an office building, where he's mistaken for the boss's kid and given free reign to wander around. Will he climb his way to the top of the corporate ladder or end up on the chopping block?

added.title: Accion Roja al Futuro
added.description: Cuando convocan a Acción Roja a una batalla épica en el futuro, Enid no está segura de lo que debe hacer.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: La busqueda del huron
added.description: Los chicos salen en busca de un escurridizo hurón en el Arroyo. Kelsey se une junto a sus amigas Stacks y Salvajessa para encontrarlo, pero le preocupa que ellas prefieran pasar tiempo juntas entre sí que con ella.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La casa de munecas embrujada
added.description: Craig y sus amigos descubren que los persigue una muñeca aterradora y su casa de muñecas embrujada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Guarderia del Arroyo
added.description: Craig y su hermana Jessica intentan administrar la guarderia del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Contrabandistas de Azucar
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP se convierten en contrabandistas para llevarle dulces a niños necesitados.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Potencial Desperdiciado
added.description: A raíz de la victoria de la temporada anterior, los ninjas se han ablandado y el Maestro Wu debe recordarles quiénes son realmente.

added.title: Classic Rock
added.description: Batman thinks he's helping a homeless old man who is being mugged on the street only to discover that the man is a powerful wizard being chased by demons in disguise. It turns out the wizard is on a mission to save Shazam from the clutches of Black Adam.

added.title: Mushroom Menace
added.description: The Mysterious Hooded Woman wants the Warriors For Hire to defend her giant pumpkin home from the dreaded Smashroom Mushroom, but Vambre and Prohyas can't complete their mission without help from Zombie Pumpkin Magisword!

added.title: Buscando Misiones
added.description: Al darse cuenta de que se han ablandado, el ninja busca una misión para reactivar su entrenamiento de Spinjitzu. Desafortunadamente, la ciudad de NINJAGO está disfrutando de un período de rara tranquilidad.

added.title: The Mystery of Loch-Mess
added.description: The Warriors are sent on a mission to Loch Mess to locate missing deliverymen only to find themselves captured as pets for the giant piggy Queen Porcina.

added.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get distracted while setting up chairs for a kids birthday party and unleash a monster that terrorizes the entire park.

added.title: Un Comienzo Dificil
added.description: iLos ninja han encontrado su búsqueda! Ahora solo tienen que llegar allí, lo que implica un viaje por carretera a través del desierto de Doom, una región supuestamente habitada por un escarabajo gigante.

added.title: Night of the Bat
added.description: Superman and other Justice League members have to battle Batman when he gets possessed by an evil Djinn, Uthool, who is intent on using the JL power core to blow a crack in Earth.

added.title: Caffeinated Concert Tickets
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby make a deal with a Coffee Bean to help them stay awake to work major overtime to pay for concert tickets.

added.title: El Vientre del Monstruo
added.description: Para reparar el Land-Bounty, el ninja debe recuperar un componente crítico del motor que ha sido tragado por un escarabajo gigante.

added.title: Case Clothed
added.description: Princess Zange hires the Warriors to be her secret service for the afternoon to go shopping, but the looting pirates of Keelhaul Cove make fashion makeovers nearly impossible to manage.

added.title: Death Punchies
added.description: Rigby learns an ultimate karate move and becomes the bully of the park.

added.title: Trampas y Como Sobrevivir a Ellas
added.description: El ninja se une a un clutch Powers renuente para entrar en una misteriosa pirámide donde desatan sin darse cuenta un antiguo mal.

added.title: Follow that Space Cab!
added.description: While Superman escorts his prisoner Mr. Mind between planets, he is attacked by Lobo who wants to collect a reward on Mind. Temporarily powered-down, Superman seeks Space Cabbie's help to get away from Lobo.

added.title: Cleanliness Is Next to Grupliness
added.description: Grup has been stinking up the entire town of Rhyboflaven, but no matter how the Warriors try to lead the little dragon to water, they can't make him bathe!

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: A Pardo le gustan los burritos. Mucho. Tanto que cuando un restaurant elabora un Burrito tamaño oso, Pardo se obliga a comer semejante obra de arte majestuosa. Lleva el burrito consigo a todas partes y lo convierte en una parte nueva y cada vez más olorosa de su vida.

added.title: Zombie King
added.description: Grundy escapes his Louisiana prison intent on using a magical crystal which will allow him to raise the dead from their graves. Only Batman and Swamp thing stand in the way of his growing zombie army.

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby lie about being astronauts in order to cut in line at a restaurant.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: Pequena graduacion
added.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

added.title: Chaqueta De Mezclilla
added.description: Los Osos encuentran una chaqueta de jean deslumbrante en un contenedor de basura. Es una de las cosas más fabulosas que jamás hayan visto, y parece convertir a aquel que la use en una persona extremadamente afortunada. Pero cuando los Osos discuten para ver quién queda a cargo de la chaqueta, empiezan a pensar que su bendición de denim se convirtió en una maldición.

added.title: Time Share
added.description: Batman and Blue Beetle have to travel back in time to stop Chronos from destroying a young Dark Knight on his very first case.

added.title: Working for Scales
added.description: Princess Zange is sick and requires a dinosaur scale for a tea remedy, but King Rexxtopher is fiercely against the Warriors stepping foot inside his Dinosaur Kingdom to get it.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Ninjas Shhh
added.description: Los Osos están hartos de la decadencia actual del protocolo en los cines. ¿Tú no lo estás? Tras autoproclamarse "la policía de los cines", se cuelan como ninjas para hacer callar a las personas que arruinan con sus malos modales la experiencia del ir al cine.

added.title: Tiara Trouble
added.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

added.title: A Small Problem
added.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he to short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

added.title: The Wrinklegruff Gals
added.description: Sick of being the tiniest kids at their new school, the girls convince Professor Utonium to create a potion to make them older! Unfortunately, when they take too much, they become senior citizens and a prime target for Mojo Jojo!

added.title: Charlie
added.description: ¿Viste cuando tienes un amigo que no entiende una indirecta? Ese es Charlie, Pie Grande. Los Osos lo conocen cuando Charlie se inscribe en un sitio web para personas que comparten su casa y se instala un fin de semana con los Osos. Charlie es el peor invitado posible para los Osos y prácticamente destruye la casa.

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Osos Habitantes
added.description: Pardo, Panda y Polar no son más que tres forasteros en busca de un camino que los lleve a la adaptación... y si pueden conseguir algo de helado (o, en lo posible, yogur helado descremado) en el camino, imucho mejor! En cada episodio se muestran las desventuras cotidianas de los osos, que buscan comida, hacen todo tipo de tonterías y lidian unos con otros y con el mundo que los rodea. Sea cual sea la situación que enfrentan, está claro que ser un oso en un mundo civilizado y moderno no es tarea sencilla.

added.title: #NoDerribenElArbol
added.description: Jessica Cruz y Pam Isley se unen para evitar que un antiguo árbol sea talado, pero ninguna se da cuenta de quien es el alter ego de la otra ni los extremos a los que llegarán para proteger lo que es importante.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #IlusionesDeGrandeza
added.description: Lista para salir de la sombra de su padre, Zatara busca la fama y el reconocimiento con una presentación para su propia audiencia en el muelle. Pero cuando su acto es tildado de fraude, ella pierde el control y accidentalmente libera terribles seres que causan estragos en el muelle.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #SuperHeroBoys Parte 1
added.description: Lo que comienza como una simple investigación por vandalismo, se transforma en una lucha territorial cuando las chicas encuentran un poderoso trío de kryptonianos decididos a dominar el mundo, y lo que es peor... iun grupo de Super Hero Boys!
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Sale el Don
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val descubren que Don Jalapeño no es realmente él mismo, depende de ellos usar el alocado libro de conspiraciones de Don para salvarlo.

added.title: #LaConvencionDeGotham
added.description: Un divertido día para Barbara Gordon y su mejor amiga Harley Quinzel en la Convención Anual de Gotham City, es puesto cabeza abajo cuando, de la nada, ila malvada Harley Quinn aparece para sembrar el caos! Por suerte para todos, Batgirl se encuentra casualmente en el área...
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: Sabelotodo
added.description: Cuando Vic accidentalmente libera malvados murciélagos de una cueva, depende de los chicos y de Don proteger el pueblo, pero la actitud de sabelotodo de Vic pone en peligro la tarea.

added.title: Amor a primera mordida
added.description: A Val le gusta una chica llamada Matty, y Vic sospecha de ella, pero Val ignora sus advertencias. Cuando Val va a su casa a cenar, ella se convierte en una Matlazihua, iy Val descubre que él es la cena!

added.title: Fashion Forward
added.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 1
added.description: The Incursean Armada, with the help of Dr. Psychobos, have invaded the Earth. (Reintroducing old Ben alien, BenMummy.)

added.title: Bezt Frends
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to extreme measures to surpass Pizza Steve as Pizza Steve's best friend.

added.title: Joke's on You, Bro!
added.description: Axel and the team turn Galileo's camouflaging pranks around on him, convincing the gullible gecko that he's permanently invisible - to disastrous results!

added.title: Rad
added.description: With Plumber agents trapped in Incursean territory, Ben and Rook must employ the services of Rad Dudesman, the roughest, toughest smuggler in the galaxy.  (Introducing Rad Dudesman, return of classic Ben alien, Eye Guy.)

added.title: Out of My Head
added.description: Axel must help Sarge and Bobbie learn to walk in each other's shoes - literally - after Luka unwittingly switches the toys' heads!

added.title: Freeze!
added.description: Axel and his team find themselves in a tough position after Ice Crusher makes it too cold for them to fight back at full speed.

added.title: King Axel
added.description: After a screening of the King Arthur tale, Axel holds out his sword and declares himself king, but when Dynamo uses his magnetism to steal the weapon and bestow it upon Masko, it casts doubt among the team over who is the true leader.

added.title: Food Around the Corner
added.description: Ben as Gravattack attempts to moderate a fragile peace treaty, but must endure the attacks of tiny alien fleas, which have inhabited his body.

added.title: The Trojan Bear
added.description: When Axel opens a subscription gift-box he didn't even order, the team finds their ranks divided by a robotic bear - or Princess SugarSalt in disguise!

added.title: Fire Man in the Hole
added.description: While hiking on a dormant volcano, Aki sets out to retrieve Ashley's lost camera and, as Mega Man, to stop Fire Man from setting off an eruption!

added.title: A Split End
added.description: After replicating Cut Man's powers, Mega Man goes on a perfectionist spree, putting him on a collision course with Cut Man himself, whose latest stint as a hairdresser hasn't helped him overcome his own compulsions.

added.title: Professor Proofed
added.description: After the Professor's latest experiment goes awry, the girls become overprotective.

added.title: All Play and No Work
added.description: Mega Man must resist the influence of a prankster bot named Chaotique, whose devil may care ideology appeals to the overworked superhero, until his friends pay the price for his dalliances.

added.title: More More More!
added.description: In order to out-muscle Guts Man, Mega Man copies the big bot's schematics, and his insatiable appetite!

added.title: De vuelta a la accion roja
added.description: Enid se alía a Acción Roja para enfrentarse a una amenaza del futuro.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Blast Resort
added.description: Mega Man must assist Blasto Woman in a heist to stop a powerful EMP emitter from falling into the wrong hands.

added.title: Back in Red Action
added.description: Enid teams up with Red Action to take on a menace from the future.

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: El Oso Troyano
added.description: Cuando Axel abre una caja de regalo de suscripción que ni siquiera ordenó, el equipo encuentra sus filas divididas por un oso robótico, io la Princesa SugarSalt disfrazada!

added.title: Ahora Te Toca a Ti, Amigo
added.description: Axel y el equipo giran las bromas de camuflaje de Galileo sobre él, convenciendo al crédulo gecko de que es permanentemente invisible, ipara obtener resultados desastrosos!

added.title: Juntos por Siempre
added.description: Connie tiene una visión muy clara de su futuro, y Steven quiere asegurarse de ser parte de esa visión.

added.title: No Me Impresiona
added.description: Cuando un Corazoncito no se siente impresionado con las hazañas del departamento del sheriff, nuestros tres héroes intentan de todo para conquistarlo.

added.title: #ElShowDeLasBestias
added.description: Cuando Babs y Kara discuten sobre cual de sus perros es mejor, deciden resolver la situación en el concurso anual de perros de Metrópolis, donde Ace, el Bati-sabueso y Krypto, el Superperro, deberán salvar el día.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Dia de Elecciones
added.description: Manzana se presenta como candidato a alcalde.

added.title: La Venganza de Bao Bao
added.description: Cuando el antiguo compañero de Mao Mao amenaza al reino, los amigos de Mao Mao tendrán que conocer su pasado para proteger el presente.

added.title: Rey Axel
added.description: Después de una proyección de la historia del Rey Arturo, Axel extiende su espada y se declara rey, pero cuando Dynamo usa su magnetismo para robar el arma y dársela a Masko, arroja dudas entre el equipo sobre quién es el verdadero líder.

added.title: Congelados
added.description: Axel y su equipo se encuentran en una posición difícil después de que Ice Crusher hace demasiado frío para que puedan defenderse a toda velocidad.

added.title: Fuera de Mi Cabeza
added.description: iAxel debe ayudar a Sarge y Bobbie a aprender a caminar en los zapatos del otro, literalmente, después de que Luka involuntariamente cambia las cabezas de los juguetes!

added.title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
added.description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

added.title: Mo' Linguish/Oops, I Did It Again
added.description: Mo' Linguish: Mojo is sentenced to do community service for Townsville and begins teaching English at the Learning Annex. Soon everyone is speaking in circles like Mojo and the town comes to a standstill./Oops, I Did It Again: When the Professor realizes that all his successful experiments are actually just accidents, he sets out to do something brilliant on purpose!

added.title: Roughing It Up/What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Roughing It Up: The girls and the Professor set out on an old-fashioned vacation to the Townsville Swamp. Trouble is, Fuzzy and his nephews are there, too./What's the Big Idea?: 20 story high Powerpuff Girls spell disaster for Townsville when they delicately try to stop Mojo from taking over.

added.title: Powerprof.
added.description: The girls are so busy fighting crime that the Professor doesn't get to see them anymore. So he creates a superhero suit for himself. Unfortunately, he starts cramping their superhero style.

added.title: Artesanias traviesas
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic libera al señor de las travesuras del interior una reliquia antigua, V y V tienen que trabajar en equipo para volver a encerrarlo.

added.title: Quintos Quinces
added.description: Victor y Valentino quieren ir a la fiesta en la piscina de un amigo el mismo día que la fiesta de quince años de su abuela, así que usan una flauta mágica que les permite teletransportarse y asistir a ambas al mismo tiempo.

added.title: Amor de hermanos
added.description: Después de romper la planta de Chata, Vic y Val deben cumplir con la tarea aparentemente fácil de reemplazarla, lo cual demuestra no serlo cuando sus disputas ponen en peligro Monte Macabro.

added.title: Dia de limpieza
added.description: Victor y Valentino adquieren un nuevo respeto por la limpieza después de que la casa de Chata los atrapa dentro de su laberinto de paredes antiguas y mágicas.

added.title: Huracan Chata
added.description: Cuando V y V descubren que las emociones de Chata controlan el agua del lago, deciden sacar ventaja y comienzan su propio negocio de piscinas de olas.

added.title: El club de los solitarios
added.description: En lugar de celebrar el Día de San Valentín, Vic y Val se atreven a explorar una mansión encantada con sus rivales, Charlene y Piña.

added.title: Victor y la Lechuza
added.description: Después de fingir una lesión para no tener que trabajar, Vic se gana la compasión de todos mientras que, sin saberlo, atrae la atención de una peligrosa criatura mítica.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val le guarda rencor a Vic, lo cual atrae sin querer a un malvado cadejo, una bestia mitológica parecida a un lobo.

added.title: Thank You for Watching the Show
added.description: When KO finds moments of his life slipping by, he begins to suspect something weird is going on.

added.title: GarQuest
added.description: Gar and KO team up for a secret mission.

added.title: Gar Trains Punching Judy
added.description: With a big fight coming up, Punching Judy turns to KO and Gar to help her prepare.

added.title: We're Captured
added.description: Boxman captures KO, Enid and Rad, but seems a little distracted.

added.title: Parents Day
added.description: It's Parents' Day at Lakewood Plaza Turbo!

added.title: Villains' Night Out
added.description: Lord Boxman forces his way into an exclusive Villains party.

added.title: Villains' Night In
added.description: While Boxman and Venomous are out, Fink is reluctantly babysat by Darrell and Shannon.

added.title: Chad and the Marathon
added.description: When Chad realizes his lazy habits might be rubbing off on Clarence, he decides to participate in the Aberdale Marathon. However, the athletic Chad doesn't know the first thing about being a runner, and must enlist the help of Clarence to train!

added.title: Chadsgiving
added.description: Clarence is excited for Thanksgiving Dinner with Chad's parents, but Chad is worried that their unusually laid back demeanor and bizarre customs will make him look irresponsible by association.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
added.description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Neighborhood Grill
added.description: Clarence is so troubled by the sight of his teacher in a social setting outside of school, he can't stop himself from intruding on her doomed blind date.

added.title: Where the Wild Chads Are
added.description: Chad takes Clarence out to the woods for some grizzly-man camping but Clarence is disappointed at the cushy set up; heaters, a hammock, even a portable TV. To make it a more rugged adventure, Clarence ditches Chad's wallet, cell phone and all their food but it may be too much wilderness for them to handle.

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: Prime Mates/Coupe D'Etat
added.description: Prime Mates: Back when Mojo Jojo tried to take over the world with primates, there was one monkey who didn't get his due: Mopey Popo. Now, Mopey is back to try and be just as evil as Mojo intended./Coupe D'Etat: When the Professor tricks out his car, the girls realize that this K.A.R.R. is taking the Professor away from them both figuratively and literally.

added.title: Lying Around the House/Bubble Boy
added.description: Lying Around The House: The girls tell little white lies that turn into a big, bad problem./Bubble Boy: Realizing that the only way to beat the Rowdyruff Boys is to join them, Bubbles takes Boomer's place in this rough-and-tumble band of boys.

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: Rebel Rebel
added.description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Sideline Dad
added.description: When the Girls start playing soccer, the Professor goes overboard.

added.title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
added.description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

added.title: Deb O'Nair
added.description: A classy queen of etiquette makes the Utoniums question their superhero way of life.

added.title: Collection Infection
added.description: Having pared down their Magisword collection, the Warriors are forced into unconventional battle choices on a dangerous mission into the Deepest Darkest Woods.

added.title: For the Love of Narwhal
added.description: Vambre rejects Darlin' Narwhal Magisword as being unfit for battle, but when Prohyas trains and brings out its full potential, Vambre resorts to improper extremes to get it back.

added.title: Suitable Armor
added.description: A veteran warrior insists that Vambre is under dressed for battle and takes it upon herself to garb Vambre in armor as Prohyas fights the beast solo without armor.

added.title: Fixing a Flonk
added.description: Wanting to stop Flonk from being an evildoer for good, Prohyas tries to find Flonk a permanent venue for his nasty comedy. Vambre, however, wants to deliver him to the cops as usual.

added.title: Ain't That a Kick in the Side?
added.description: After Witch Way teases Prohyas by calling him, "Vambre's sidekick," Prohyas intensifies his efforts to prove them wrong.

added.title: Just Friends
added.description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.

added.title: Rigby Goes to Prom
added.description: Rigby asks Eileen to prom. But in order to get there, he has to sneak his Dad's car out of the garage and get it back in one piece.

added.title: Power Tower
added.description: Muscle Man wants to win the bodybuilding competition at his gym.

added.title: Family BBQ
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a handshake from Margaret's dad.

added.title: The Best Burger in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to finish their chores before they can have burgers.

added.title: Trucker Hall of Fame
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Muscle Man get to the Big Rig Museum to spread his dad's hat's ashes.

added.title: Dizzy
added.description: M and R help Pops get over his fear of public speaking.

added.title: Benson Be Gone
added.description: Mordecai sees Pops naked and goes on a quest to unsee what he has seen.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: Washington B.C.
added.description: Ben must use the Omnitrix to transform into alien heroes to battle Dr. Amino and his transmorphed dinosaurs running rampant in Washington DC.

added.title: The Krakken
added.description: While stopped at a lakefront campsite, Ben has a chance encounter with a Loch Ness type sea monster called a Krakken, controlled by an evil poacher.

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Many Happy Returns
added.description: Gwen and Kevin pay Ben a surprise visit, but does Kevin's strange behavior have anything to do with an angry Tetramand princess, or her father's fleet of warships prepared to attack the Earth?

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Mr. Smoothy's
added.description: The Plumbers' resident geniuses, Blukic and Driba set off to find some smoothies meanwhile Ben and Rook try to stop Trombipulor from gaining the source of absolute power.

added.title: Arrested Development
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Showdown Part 2
added.description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

added.title: Vilgax Must Croak
added.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

added.title: Rules of Engagement
added.description: Princess Looma returns to claim Ben as her husband, and she's not going to let anyone stand in her way!  (Featuring Julie and Ship.)

added.title: La Dama
added.description: Los niños descubren que Papá se ha vestido como una mujer para conocer amigos.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Vecino
added.description: Gumball y Darwin intentan averiguar el nombre de su vecino, el tipo de los cuernos. Pero, por accidente, develan su identidad falsa de testigo protegido.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Recibo
added.description: Papá pierde un paquete y se ve envuelto en una pelea cada vez mayor con el repartidor.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Gemacaciones
added.description: Greg y las Gemas llevan a Steven de vacaciones para ayudarlo a relajarse.

added.title: Los Verdaderos Orijanes
added.description: Robin trata de contar la verdadera historia del origen de los Jóvenes Titanes.

added.title: Hoyuelitos
added.description: Raven compite en un certamen de belleza, creyendo que es la forma de reconectarse con su padre.

added.title: El Guardia Norm
added.description: Cuando Tabes se va a una conferencia, los Osos deben lidiar con su reemplazo, el guardabosques Norm.

added.title: Bebes Serpientes
added.description: Charlie adopta a unas serpientes bebé a pesar de que los Osos creen que no está listo para la paternidad.

added.title: Baile Demoniaco
added.description: Trigon invita a Raven a su baile de graduación, y ella lleva a los demás Titanes para molestarlo.

added.title: Banda de revoltosos
added.description: Una pandilla de niños revoltosos adopta a Polar bebé.

added.title: El Cumpleanos de Panda
added.description: Para el cumpleaños de Panda, los Osos intentan ayudarlo a conocer a su banda favorita de K-pop, Monsta X.

added.title: El Senor de las Amapolas
added.description: Pardo y las Amapolas van a acampar a una isla, pero pronto quedan abandonados.

added.title: Hermanos en la Ciudad
added.description: Los osos protagonizan un reality show con Pablo, Tom e Isaac.

added.title: Googs
added.description: Los osos ganan un tour a las oficinas de una importante empresa.

added.title: Escuadron Osuno
added.description: Tabes permite que los osos tomen su lugar para que vayan a la ciudad y atrapen a un ladrón.

added.title: Yo Mayordomo
added.description: Los Osos usan un oso robótico que los ayuda con las tareas domésticas. Pero las cosas se complican cuando pierden el control del robot.

added.title: Osos Padrinos
added.description: Los osos deben cumplir sus tareas de padrinos en la boda de Darrell.

added.title: Duelo en la Piscina
added.description: Unikitty y la pandilla se están divirtiendo mucho en la piscina pública, hasta que intentan que Perricornio nade en la parte profunda con ellos. A Perricornio le da muchísimo miedo ir a lo más profundo. Ahora Unikitty y la banda deben ayudarlo a superar su miedo para que se divierta al máximo en la piscina. Mientras tanto, Master Frown y Brock están tramando un plan para arruinar la diversión de todos: quitar el tapón de la piscina. Ahora Perricornio debe dominar su miedo para detener a los que quieren estropear la diversión.

added.title: Letras Desastrosas
added.description: La pandilla está planeando una sorpresa para Puppycorn, así que deletrean las cosas cuando hablan para que él no se entere. Desesperado por saber lo que dicen, Puppycorn encuentra un libro mágico que cree que lo ayudará a aprender a deletrear, ipero sin saberlo, el libro le enseña a lanzar hechizos! ¿Se dará cuenta Puppycorn de que el conocimiento es poder, y de que algunos secretos se guardan por una razón?

added.title: Atrapados en el paraiso
added.description: Unikitty y la banda aterrizaron de emergencia en una isla fabulosa. Todo es muy bonito y nadie quiere irse hasta que Richard los convence de que tienen que volver al Reino y asumir sus responsabilidades. Por desgracia, alguien sabotea cada intento de escapar de la isla. Ahora deben encontrar al culpable para asegurar su regreso a casa.

added.title: Volcan
added.description: Un volcán súper gruñón aparece en el reino. Por eso, Unikitty lleva a la banda a una misión épica para alegrarlo con una de las flores de FeeBee antes de que entre en erupción y destruya el reino. Pero FeeBee no tiene ganas de compartir sus queridas flores, y trata de sabotear la misión. ¿Será capaz Unikitty de convencerla de los beneficios de compartir para salvar el reino de la destrucción?

added.title: Mision Gar
added.description: El Sr. Gar y KO hacen equipo para una misión secreta.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Una Nueva Vida
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín abandonan sus hogares y se mudan a la ciudad, donde se conocen por primera vez.

added.title: Ganas de Explorar
added.description: La misión de Craig de mapear el Arroyo entero los lleva a él y a sus amigos a arboleda traicionera de Hiedra Venenosa
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Equipo Perfecto
added.description: A Cebollín le preocupa que su relación con Manzana corra peligro cuando un gato callejero entra en su vida.

added.title: El Dia Divertido de Falafel
added.description: Cuando Falafel decide empacar sus cosas e ir a la ciudad, Manzana y Cebollín deben convencerlo de quedarse.

added.title: 4 a 1
added.description: El temor de Cebollín a las multitudes amenaza el éxito de su equipo de baloncesto.

added.title: Fiesta en la Cuadra
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben ser más astutos que un pato malvado que se apoderó del techo de su edificio.

added.title: Nos Capturaron
added.description: Box-man captura a K.O., Enid y Rad, pero parece un poco distraído.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Punos Fuertes
added.description: Harto de perder cuando juega a los videojuegos contra su padre, Craig busca entrenarse en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: No Me Ataques, Amigo
added.description: Ben y Billy Billones, su archienemigo, se enfrentan en un duelo por la supremacía en Laser Town, el parque de simulación de armas láser. Pero cuando, sin darse cuenta, Billy desata una rebelión robótica, y los lásers pasan de tocar a desintegrar, isu juego infantil se convierte en una guerra sin cuartel! Los enemigos descubren que deben dejar de lado sus diferencias y unirse para poder salir con vida...iy salvar al resto del planeta!

added.title: Que No Pare La Musica
added.description: Ben y Gwen están entusiasmados por ir al concierto de EDM en el Día de la Tierra en Portland, hasta que Lord Decibel, el villano que manipula el sonido, se apodera del concierto cuando intenta usar el sonido como un arma para destruir el planeta.

added.title: Penny Ruda
added.description: Ben visita el Gran Desfile Anual Big Bacon, pero Penny Heaven, su "amiga" de la infancia, se reúne con la familia para estropear la diversión de Ben con su obsesión por la seguridad. Mientras Ben esquiva las medidas de seguridad extremas de Penny, devela un plan de los HERMANOS BUGG, ique intentan robar helio de los globos del desfile para usarlos en robos de bancos! La insistencia de Penny convierte el ataque en un secuestro accidental, de modo que Ben no solo debe impedir el robo sino también salvar a su "supervisora de seguridad" menos querida.

added.title: Zombozolandia
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max vuelven a su parque de diversiones favorito... irenovado y rebautizado como AdrenaWORLD! Por desgracia, iel nuevo gerente es Zombozo, y su trío de secuaces! Zombozo planea hipnotizar a todos los visitantes del parque para formar un ejército criminal. Ben tiene que dejar de lado su deseo de subir a todos los juegos del parque y arreglar las cosas.

added.title: Olvideti
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max van de excursión en busca de un Forgeti legendario, un yeti que hace que las personas se olviden de que lo vieron, pero cuando el Doctor Ánimo reúne a los Forgeti para su plan de robar bancos sin que nadie los recuerde, Ben aprende muy pronto que el Forgeti es más que un simple mito.

added.title: Dia de Playa
added.description: Unikitty y la pandilla se preparan para un día divertido en la playa, pero cuando Master Frown aparece como socorrista para arruinar sus planes en la arena, Unikitty y la pandilla se embarcan en una búsqueda para encontrar el legendario lugar perfecto, lejos del dominio tiránico de Frown. Pero ¿podrán llegar allí antes de que Frown lo reclame para él o su búsqueda se convertirá en un verdadero fastidio playero?

added.title: Max Al Maximo
added.description: Mientras Ben, Gwen y Max van de excursión a una cascada, los Hermanos Bugg regresan con el plan de duplicar a Diamante. Pero cuando su arma láser clonadora le dispara a Max por error-y lo multiplica infinitamente-, Gwen y Ben deben juntar a todos los Maxes y ahuyentar a los Hermanos Bugg a la vez.

added.title: Magia Tragica
added.description: Cuando Richard monta un espectáculo de magia amateur, la Dra. Fox se obsesiona por descubrir cómo se hacen esos trucos que desafían la ciencia. Pero mientras se propone usar todo su intelecto para encontrar formas experimentales de hacer los trucos que vio en la fiesta del cachorro, ¿acaso arruinará accidentalmente el asombro de la magia?

added.title: Cortando Camino
added.description: Ben habla con Geezer Bob para hacer alguna tarea de jardín y así ganar un poco de dinero, pero cuando Ben se transforma en Upgrade para convertir la podadora de césped en una cortadora súper rápida, por accidente despierta la ira de los vecinos gnomos de Bob: los diminutos y aterradoramente obstinados duendes de Billy Bob.

added.title: Xingo
added.description: Ben está muy interesado en una maratón de Spazz, su dibujo animado favorito, pero cuando se transforma en Upgrade para mejorar la señal de televisión, el protagonista de Spazz salta de su dimensión animada hacia la nuestra...iy trae consigo un caos demente!

added.title: Senor Casero
